window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><i>The Senate Intelligence Committee Summary Report on Torture</i> is a public document belonging to the American people, arising from the Senate investigation into the CIA’s Interrogation and Detention Program. The summary report is more commonly known by its shorthand: <i>The Torture Report</i>. The Senate Intelligence Committee made public this document, with redactions, on December 9, 2009. The events surrounding its investigation, writing, and publication are now the subject of Scott Z. Burns’ film <i>The Report</i>, an Amazon Original (in theaters on 11/15 and on Amazon Prime 11/29 from Amazon Studios). Here, you can hear the report in its entirety, with selected footnotes - omitting those sections that are yet to be declassified - as read by members of the cast of the film. Also included is a special introduction by Daniel J. Jones, the lead investigator of the <i>Senate Intelligence Committee Report on Torture</i>.&nbsp;</p> <p>The introduction to this audiobook is written and read by the lead investigator, Daniel J. Jones. The body of this audiobook is read by the cast members of the movie <i>The Report</i> including Annette Bening, Jon Hamm, Sarah Goldberg, Michael C. Hall, Douglas Hodge, Fajer Al-Kaisi, Ted Levine, Jennifer Morrison, Tim Blake Nelson, Linda Powell, Scott Shepherd, T. Ryder Smith, Corey Stoll, Maura Tierney, and Joanne Tucker.</p>"; 
